Colom has approved Portilla's release to the United States.
On Tuesday, President Álvaro Colom announced that he had made progress on the issue of former President Alfons Portillo, to be held accountable in the United States for a conspiracy to launder $70 million.
This is the end of the process for Guatemala to respond at the request of the northern country requesting the extradition of Portilla in order to judge him.
