There was an eviction of an occupied house where giant parties were held
Intruders took 11 out of 13 apartments in a building in Balmes, 51
12 occupiers left the house yesterday at noon without resisting
All indications are that the nightmare experienced by the number 51 neighbors on Balmes Street is finally over.
Twelve people voluntarily left the building at noon yesterday, illegally inhabited and organized giant parties that woke the neighbors, leaving the building under court orders and without having to interfere with the police.
After the operation was completed, the lock on the door was replaced to prevent a recurrence of the situation.
"From now on, the entrance will be guarded," said the warden.
The occupations who occupied 11 of the 13 flats in the building - the remaining ones are inhabited - took away all electrical and partly water equipment, in addition they painted walls and left behind garbage of all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
Huge parties took place in the first three apartments, which lasted up to two days and woke up the other tenants.
Next to the building is a disco, Balmes 51, which was also damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, explained to Europa Press that, while the building was occupied, sales fell by 80%.
The owner of the disco points out that the occupation of the building made it unfairly competitive because they sold drinks for 3 euros, while it costs 10 at the disco.
In addition, the owner of the entertainment company had to respond to the neighbors’ noise lawsuits. However, the problems were not caused by discos, but by the residents of the occupied house and especially by those who participated in the organized parties, whose frequency and intensity has increased in recent weeks, according to the upset inhabitants of the surrounding area.
The owner of the disco explained that the problems were so great that they even agreed with the owner of the building and for nine months she has forgiven her rent.
City police have also confirmed that they have received more complaints from their neighbors over the past few weeks about the situation.
