Park or mountains?
Architects met on the occasion of a procedure that carries more than controversy about fees
The municipal tender for 16 gates again opens up a debate about the role of Collserola park in Barcelona.
In the mid-1980s, at the peak of the already extinct corporation Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), the municipality printed several pamphlets to support Collserola Park.
The flyer defined the mountain as a large park of Metropolitan Barcelona.
What's more, it was supplemented by a numerical comparison with New York Central Park.
After CMB disappeared in 1987, the park returned to the mind of many as the top border of Barcelona. The Catalonian capital is one of the few that are not oriented north-south axis, but up (mountain) - down (sea).
Collserola's qualifications as a natural park go that way.
The reference was no longer Central Park, but Yellowstone with boars instead of Yogi Bear.
This was the position until September when the town hall announced a mega competition consisting of 16 auditions for the same number of entrance gates to Collserola.
Of course, the gate is recording the idea of the park.
It's either this or someone's trying to place the gate on the field.
So there is only one question: Collserola, park or mountain?
During the competition, both in terms of purely organizational and on the basis of a reflection on the city, this question becomes the central theme of all Barcelona architects.
It's already a subject as fresh as when two members of this old caste of the chosen ones shake hands at the meeting in the elevator.
And it was this act that triggered one of the rare matches between what the three Barcelona architects and the preeminent university professors think.
Miguel Roldan, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: the tender has its merits.
According to Roldán, after the question of the bay side began, "it is necessary" to discuss the "mountain side", so Ildefons Cerd's speech on green apples was not reached to the end.
"We must base ourselves on the principle that the largest park in Barcelona is the beach.
Amongst other things, its great availability.
Collserola is more complex", said the architect for whom the name "gates to Collserola" carries a "lexicological trap": we must not imagine them "as entrances to the park, but rather as defining zones where it is possible to operate".
Modol, like Roldan and Bayona with experience in the world of urbanism, qualifies the proposal as an "intellectual challenge" offering "some dangers".
The danger resulting from the "uncertainty presented today by the project of the public place" after the experience of the 1980s, which had in the Forum area "its swan singing".
The first concern is the very definition of the boundaries where it should be built.
"To define something means to take the next step", that is, basically, to move on.
"It is necessary to bear in mind the new urban and planning tools, because the current ones (with reference to the General Metropolitan Plan (PGM)) can cause a real disaster".
If we look more closely at the question, Modol believes that the valley slope of Collserola can be "considered as a park", but not the Barcelona part, for purely topographic reasons.
Modol also recalled that there is already work done by Patronat de Collserola, which "can't end up in a dump", although he welcomes the fact that the town hall offers its grémium, that it will intervene in the project from the "first moment".
Moreover, he understands that the proximity of the mountain and the city is a sort of pass allowing architects to engage in the debate, but "doubts", that it should be this technical profile, which will lead the multidisciplinary teams ("it's all about skills", adds), which must be created: "Architekti should only be tools".
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question given by the name of this game is complex, because there is no global vision of Collserol in the tender documentation: "16 competitions have been announced that deal with all the axis of the mountain - the sea, but there is no longitudinal study that looks at the area and understands it as a whole".
This causes at least him to sign up for all 16 competitions.
Otherwise, the project of one gate may refer to the concept and definition of the architect of the neighbouring gate.
In his view, the City Hall should guarantee that the zone located immediately above Ronda de Dalt should secure the entire length of the equipment zone, which would ensure a smooth transition between the city and the greenery.
